raman munjal vidya mandir is an educational institution located in sidhrawali village in the gurgaon district of haryana, india. situated at the 67th milestone on delhi-jaipur highway (nh 8), the foundation was laid in 1992  by the munjal family (who owns hero group) in the loving memory of the director of hero honda motors ltd. (now hero motocorp ltd.), late mr. raman kant munjal. the institution was established in order to provide education to the rural people of nearby areas to help them attain a better lifestyle and to promote knowledge at the most basic level, something that can advance the whole country. it is maintained by the raman kant munjal foundation (rkmf), whose chairperson is mrs. renu munjal.